OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F363A1782134325
OL,3,C'I didn't want to risk it': Hodgkinson
OL,4,C'healthy' after UK Championships exit
OL,6,FHodgkinson was laid off for 376 days
OL,7,Fwith injury, much of it hamstring-
OL,8,Frelated, before returning last August
OL,9,Fto set a world-leading 800m time, then
OL,10,Fclaimed bronze at the 2025 world
OL,11,Fchampionships in Tokyo having raced
OL,12,Fjust twice that season before
OL,13,Ftravelling to Japan.
OL,15,FIt was a layoff she later described as
OL,16,Fa "s***show" so her reluctance to risk
OL,17,Fanything after announcing her London
OL,18,Fintentions is understandable,
OL,19,Fparticularly after she was beaten by
OL,20,FSwiss rival Audrey Werro earlier this
OL,21,Fmonth.
OL,26,@xD@COUxD@LO]
